OL,3,CBlue plaque unveiled for Blackpool's
OL,4,Cmost famous clown
OL,6,FCharlie was the resident clown at the
OL,7,FTower Circus from 1939 to 1979
OL,8,Fdelighting audiences with his unique
OL,9,Fblend of music, comedy, and charm.
OL,11,FOver the decades, he became a
OL,12,Fhousehold name and drew more
OL,13,Fholidaymakers to Blackpool than any
OL,14,Fother entertainer of his time.
OL,16,FHis son, also called Charlie, unveiled
OL,17,Fthe plaque at Blackpool Tower Circus.
OL,19,FHe said": "I'm really really proud, he
OL,20,Floved Blackpool and said the people
OL,21,Fwere so warming"
